The TLS/GPST peer in test/m2_gp_transport_interop_test.go is an original test
implementation based only on wire behavior in auth-globalprotect.c and gpst.c
from OpenConnect commit 2035601b64a5360a46d18e08937e7f654b3230f2.

The relevant observed contracts are portal and gateway request paths, JNLP
argument positions, getconfig and HIP form fields, the raw GET followed by the
12-byte START_TUNNEL marker, and the 16-byte GPST frame header. No OpenConnect
code is copied into the peer.

